title: Aleksandr Kutitsky
text:
Aleksandr Olegovich Kutitsky (; born 1 January 2002) is a Russian <a href="association%20football">football</a> player who plays for <a href="FC%20Dynamo%20Moscow">FC Dynamo Moscow</a>.
Club career.
He was first included in the senior squad of <a href="FC%20Dynamo%20Moscow">FC Dynamo Moscow</a> in November 2020 and subsequently joined them for their January 2021 training camp.
He made his debut for <a href="FC%20Dynamo%20Moscow">FC Dynamo Moscow</a> on 20 February 2021 in a <a href="Russian%20Cup%20%28football%29">Russian Cup</a> game against <a href="FC%20Spartak%20Moscow">FC Spartak Moscow</a>. He substituted <a href="Sergei%20Parshivlyuk">Sergei Parshivlyuk</a> in the 82nd minute of a 2–0 home victory.
He made his <a href="Russian%20Premier%20League">Russian Premier League</a> debut for Dynamo on 23 July 2021 in a game against <a href="FC%20Rostov">FC Rostov</a>, he substituted <a href="Nikola%20Moro">Nikola Moro</a> in the 75th minute.
